{"questionId":"25669","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> has a vertical asymptote and a horizontal asymptote.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the equation of the horizontal asymptote.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25669","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ2.4a.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down the equation of the horizontal asymptote.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.8—Reciprocal and simple rational functions, equations of asymptotes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}